00:35:48.390 --> 00:35:51.430
My question goes out to--

00:35:51.430 --> 00:35:53.140
it's for adults but
also for children.

00:35:53.140 --> 00:35:55.710
Can you give us words and
advice in overcoming a

00:35:55.710 --> 00:35:59.140
challenging situation or whether
it's music, writing,

00:35:59.140 --> 00:36:01.780
or just in life in general?

00:36:01.780 --> 00:36:09.520
MICHAEL FRANTI: Well, I think
that if you get yourself out

00:36:09.520 --> 00:36:14.290
of your comfort zone a lot of
the time, then it becomes more

00:36:14.290 --> 00:36:18.150
familiar crossing over those
lines where you don't feel

00:36:18.150 --> 00:36:21.000
comfortable or where
you feel scared.

00:36:21.000 --> 00:36:22.300
I practice yoga.

00:36:22.300 --> 00:36:25.840
And in our practice of yoga,
we put ourselves into

00:36:25.840 --> 00:36:26.990
uncomfortable positions.

00:36:26.990 --> 00:36:29.530
And we learn how to breathe
while we're going through

00:36:29.530 --> 00:36:32.400
these really intense
stretches.

00:36:32.400 --> 00:36:38.210
And to quiet our mind and say,
I'm not going to listen to

00:36:38.210 --> 00:36:40.660
this voice that's saying I'm
not good enough or I'm not

00:36:40.660 --> 00:36:44.140
limber enough or I'm too
tired or whatever--

00:36:44.140 --> 00:36:48.140
and we practice the exercise
so that when we get into

00:36:48.140 --> 00:36:50.820
uncomfortable situations in
our day to day life, they

00:36:50.820 --> 00:36:52.260
become easier.

00:36:52.260 --> 00:36:55.390
And they're still not.

00:36:55.390 --> 00:36:57.710
It's still always hard.

00:36:57.710 --> 00:37:03.340
But writing a book is something
that I never

00:37:03.340 --> 00:37:05.000
imagined I would do.

00:37:05.000 --> 00:37:07.150
But I made a five year
plan at one point.

00:37:07.150 --> 00:37:09.710
And I said, there's a few things
that I want to do.

00:37:09.710 --> 00:37:11.080
I want to write a book.

00:37:11.080 --> 00:37:13.090
I want to make a film.

00:37:13.090 --> 00:37:16.570
I want to start a yoga school.

00:37:16.570 --> 00:37:22.540
And I wanted to get my band
to a certain level of

00:37:22.540 --> 00:37:26.440
musicianship and get ourselves
out touring at a certain level

00:37:26.440 --> 00:37:27.940
and had goals in that regard.

00:37:27.940 --> 00:37:31.270
And just to write them down,
those goals, was really

00:37:31.270 --> 00:37:32.620
helpful for me.

00:37:32.620 --> 00:37:37.150
And then I said, I'm not going
to prioritize them in terms of

00:37:37.150 --> 00:37:39.010
what's most important, because
they're all really

00:37:39.010 --> 00:37:40.280
important to me.

00:37:40.280 --> 00:37:42.970
But I prioritized
them in terms of

00:37:42.970 --> 00:37:44.520
what was most imminent.

00:37:44.520 --> 00:37:46.870
So in order to become a better
musician, I needed to take

00:37:46.870 --> 00:37:47.750
guitar lessons.

00:37:47.750 --> 00:37:51.060
So that became in the A pile.

00:37:51.060 --> 00:37:53.010
And then there was the
B pile of things and

00:37:53.010 --> 00:37:53.980
the C pile of things.

00:37:53.980 --> 00:37:58.610
So writing stuff down and then
creating a priority of--

00:37:58.610 --> 00:38:00.150
I need to-- if I'm going
to write a book, I

00:38:00.150 --> 00:38:02.500
got to do this first.

00:38:02.500 --> 00:38:04.160
And then I got to find the
illustrator second.

00:38:04.160 --> 00:38:06.430
Then I got to figure out
a way to publish it.

